<span id="freeTextContainer2134888240687028891">This book is so damn heartbreaking...<br/> <br/>This is the first James Baldwin book that I have ever read and... my first impression was that he was such an amazing writer! <br/><br/>Once I started reading this small book, I just couldn&apos;t stop myself and I ended up reading it in one sitting.<br/><br/>I love how the characters were so realistically developed. I would say this one is a classic for a reason. <br/><br/>The story is set in the 1950s in Paris where one character staying away from home falls for a bartender. Things get comp</span>
  <span id="freeText2134888240687028891" style="display:none">This book is so damn heartbreaking...<br /> <br />This is the first James Baldwin book that I have ever read and... my first impression was that he was such an amazing writer! <br /><br />Once I started reading this small book, I just couldn't stop myself and I ended up reading it in one sitting.<br /><br />I love how the characters were so realistically developed. I would say this one is a classic for a reason. <br /><br />The story is set in the 1950s in Paris where one character staying away from home falls for a bartender. Things get complicated as this character is caught in between his morals and beliefs, decides to marry woman ultimately. <br /><br />But the consequences of all this leading to a tragic ending and heartbreaks.<br /><br />The story deals with sexual identity and several social issues, most importantly how the gay community was looked upon those days. <br /><br />Sadly, such issues are still prevailing. And yes, for that matter I would always support the LGBTQ community 🙋<br /><br />However, I would say this is a must read. I would say the best parts are the dialogues between the woman and the main character towards the end of the book.<br /><br />So many quotable lines! This is one of those few books which made me annotate and actually underline sentences 📝<br /><br />The only parts where I didn't like were how women were described in the book.</span>
